20 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Expungement from central registry. (1) An individual listed in the
21 central registry may request to have the individual's name expunged from the central registry by submitting a
22 written request to the department accompanied by an affidavit sworn to by a person with personal knowledge
23 stating facts sufficient to show that there is good cause for expungement. Good cause includes but is not
24 limited to:
25 (a) newly discovered evidence that a substantiated report of child abuse or neglect is inaccurate;
26 (b) evidence that the requester no longer poses a risk and that no significant public purpose is
